         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Installation of Payment Entry Systems and the External Management of Public Conveniences</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>DN332228</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="50760000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>East Lindsey District Council wish to formally notify suitable suppliers of a forthcoming contract opportunity for undertaking the installation of payment entry systems and the external management / operation of Public Conveniences within the district in Lincolnshire, UK.</P>
               <P>The Council are currently exploring ways to achieve savings against current operational costs and also achieve a potential income, whilst at the same time providing suitable public convenience provision throughout the district.</P>
               <P>The provisional procurement timetable for the contract is as follows:</P>
               <P>— Tender Period: 29.6.2018 to 20.9.2018.</P>
               <P>— Contract Start: January 2019.</P>
               <P>To find out more information a supplier open day will be provisionally held on the 18.4.2018 at Tedder Hall, Manby Park, Louth, Lincolnshire, LN11 8HP and those who wish to attend should make a prior appointment by sending an email to: scott.ashdown@e-lindsey.gov.uk</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Suppliers will be required to install payment entry systems at all locations with options for providing a fully managed service including income collection, cleaning, maintenance and all other operational costs.</P>
                  <P>It is intended that 13 nº. Public Conveniences located at Skegness, Mablethorpe, Sutton on Sea and Louth will be included within the contract, which will have an anticipated duration of 10 years with a further option to extend.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>2018-06-29</DATE_PUBLICATION_NOTICE>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
